title: African-Americans and Latinos are more likely to be at risk for depression than whites

title_detail.value: African-Americans and Latinos are more likely to be at risk for depression than whites

summary: A new study shows that African-Americans and Latinos are significantly more likely to experience serious depression than whites, but chronic stress does not seem to explain these differences.
